news.title: Experts call for adopting low-carbon building materials for a sustainable future
news.para: Experts at an IIT Bhubaneswar workshop emphasised the adoption of low-carbon building materials for a sustainable built environment in Odisha. They called for policies, research, and green entrepreneurship to accelerate this transition, highlighting the state's rapid urban expansion and infrastructure goals. Officials stressed the responsibility of engineers and policymakers in ensuring environmentally sound growth and supporting sustainable materials.

news.title: Tamil Nadu's land reforms department issues instructions for record maintenance
news.para: The land reforms department has issued a circular to district collectorates mandating improved record maintenance following criticism from the state information commission. Instructions cover classification, storage, and marking of documents to ensure easy accessibility and long life, addressing issues that led to RTI petition denials.

news.title: Chandigarh completes drone data collection for NAKSHA project
news.para: Chandigarh has successfully completed drone-based data collection for the NAKSHA project across 15 sectors and five villages, creating accurate digital base maps. The administration is now proceeding with data validation, integrating ownership records, and generating urban property cards, with a focus on citizen verification via a digital platform.

news.title: Overhaul housing index compilation method: Statistics ministry
news.para: India's statistics ministry is set to overhaul the housing index compilation for the Consumer Price Index (CPI). Rent data will now be collected monthly, and the index will cover both rural and urban areas. The move aims to create a more accurate reflection of housing costs by excluding government accommodations and focusing on actual rental market transactions.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder, assistant arrested for cheating contractor of ₹10 crore
news.para: Mumbai Police arrested builder Neeraj Kakad and his assistant for allegedly cheating a contractor of Rs 9.57 crore and threatening him with violence. The contractor was promised a flat as compensation for structural work on a housing project but was denied ownership and payment.

news.title: Partial OCs for Greater Noida projects that paid 25% advance under rehabilitation policy
news.para: Greater Noida Authority will now grant partial occupancy and completion certificates to developers who have made advance payments under the UP government's rehabilitation policy. This move aims to provide immediate relief to thousands of homebuyers and developers by allowing possession in proportion to dues paid, addressing procedural delays that have stalled projects for years.

news.title: SC declines plea to de-seal commercial premises at Delhi's New Rajinder Nagar
news.para: The Supreme Court has turned down a request to unseal a contested commercial property located in New Rajinder Nagar Market. Following this decision, the court mandated the Municipal Corporation of Delhi to issue a fresh inspection notice, which will outline any violations and applicable charges for conversion and penalties.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers posts net profit of ₹47.91 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers reported a net consolidated profit of ₹47.91 crore for Q2 FY26, a significant turnaround from a loss of ₹14.01 crore in the previous year. The company's total income also saw a substantial increase of 107.14% to ₹33.06 crore. Business development momentum continues with substantial GDV additions, and the industrial business is showing healthy traction.

news.title: Amaravati construction must be completed on time: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister N Chandrababu Naidu has instructed officials to speed up the construction of Amaravati. He emphasized timely completion of all works. The Chief Minister also reviewed ongoing beautification and farmer plot distribution. He assured farmers their returnable plots would be registered without delay. Naidu plans to review progress every fifteen days.

news.title: Table Space leases over 5.4 lakh sq ft workspaces across NCR
news.para: Table Space has significantly expanded its presence in the NCR, leasing over 5.4 lakh sq ft of office space. New centers have been established in Delhi's Aerocity and multiple locations in Gurugram, boosting the company's NCR portfolio to over 2.2 million sq ft and adding more than 3,000 ready-to-move-in seats.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance net profit rises 24.50% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance India reported a robust 24.50% growth in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹226.54 crore. The company's total income also saw a significant increase of 27.44%. With disbursements growing 24% quarter-on-quarter and a medium-term AUM target of ₹25,000 crore, Aptus aims to sustain over 25% growth.

news.title: Jaipur smart city to replicate model in six more towns in Rajasthan
news.para: Jaipur Smart City Limited, struggling with its own unfinished projects, has been tasked with developing six new cities. Despite significant investment, many of Jaipur's smart city initiatives remain incomplete or neglected, raising concerns about the expanded mandate. Maintenance issues and a lack of visible 'smart' features plague completed projects.

news.title: ACC posts net profit of ₹1,119.26 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: ACC, part of Adani Group, reported a significant surge in net consolidated profit after tax to ₹1,119.26 crore in Q2 FY26, a substantial increase from ₹199.70 crore in the previous year. The company's total income also grew by 28.42% to ₹6,155.35 crore. ACC remains debt-free, with plans to commission new grinding units and expand its ready-mix concrete business.

news.title: Rajasthan: RIICO offers 6,000 plots under direct allotment scheme
news.para: RIICO has launched the sixth phase of its direct allotment scheme for investors who signed MoUs during the Rising Rajasthan Global Investment Summit. This phase offers 6,000 industrial plots across 100 areas until October 14, with special reservations for various categories.

news.title: About 20,000 villagers hold protest against formation of Himmatnagar development body
news.para: Thousands of villagers in Sabarkantha district are protesting the proposed Himmatnagar Urban Development Authority. They demand the scrapping of the notification, citing the acquisition of agricultural land from 11 villages. The protest has been ongoing for 40 days. Villagers have issued a 15-day ultimatum to the government. They plan an indefinite fast if their demands are not met.

news.title: Rising population in cities pose challenge for urbanisation: Housing minister
news.para: Union Minister Manohar Lal Khattar recently convened with leaders from southern states to address the escalating issue of urban growth. Key discussions revolved around improving vital infrastructure like roads, drainage, and metro systems.

news.title: Redevelopment won’t rob anybody of residence rights: West Bengal CM
news.para: Kolkata's Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee reassured residents of old buildings. Redevelopment will protect their rights. She urged traders to reduce plastic use to prevent fires. The Chief Minister also inaugurated a project to shift electric wires underground. A similar project is planned for Kolkata. Grievances against port authorities are being addressed.

news.title: Strict action against PGs and hostels without licences in Bengaluru
news.para: According to the BECC, a large number of PG accommodations and hostels are functioning in violation of civic norms and safety regulations.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth ₹110 crore of Rohtas group
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has provisionally attached immovable properties worth Rs 110.05 crore in Lucknow, linked to a money laundering case involving Rohtas Project Limited. The probe, initiated based on 83 FIRs, revealed promoters allegedly diverted buyer funds to purchase land through associate entities, defrauding hundreds of investors.

news.title: SC stays GST demand on real estate joint development pacts
news.para: In a pivotal ruling, the Supreme Court has granted a temporary reprieve against a Goods and Services Tax demand related to a joint development agreement for a real estate project. This judicial decision may reshape the landscape for developers and landowners across the country.
